  "bio_raw": "She has more than 6 years of professional experience working in various sectors covering the academia, industry, consultancy, and development sector. She holds a master’s degree in Environmental Management and policy from Lund University, Sweden, prior to that she did her MSc and BSc (Hon’s) from University of Dhaka, Bangladesh. She is interested in combining theory and practice to solve real world environmental issues. She was an adjunct faculty member in State University of Bangladesh from 2013-2016 where she taught Economic Geography. She is currently teaching introduction to sustainable Development at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh. She is also a facilitator of a France based Climate Education Initiative -Climate Fresk.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Climate Change Mitigation, Renewable Energy, Sharing Economy, Adoption of AI and Big Data, Environmental Impact Assessment."
